main event: Two objects were observed over the air force base in Udine, Italy on July 10, 1958 around 5:30 p.m. The witnesses included Signor Bartolo Salvatore and other civilian personnel.
interesting points: The sighting was reported to the Air Force, but the Air Force files did not contain information about this specific incident.

There were requests for information about two other sightings in the Chicago area - one in Elmwood Park in 1957 and one in Des Plaines in 1958, but the Air Force was unable to locate records for those incidents.
The Air Force concluded that a sighting reported on July 20, 1958 over a civilian aircraft was likely a balloon.
The Air Force investigated a sighting in Janesville, Wisconsin on June 10, 1961 that was reported by the Civilian U.F.O. Research organization.
There were several other reported sightings from August 1959 that the Air Force had insufficient data to evaluate.
witnesses: Signor Bartolo Salvatore and other civilian personnel
